quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  16,111,"The Day that every self will come up disputing for it self, and every self will be paid in full for what it has done, and they will not be done any injustice"
  16,112,"And Allah has struck a similitude: a town that was secure (and) well composed, its provision coming up to it opulently from every place, then it disbelieved (i.e., they were unthankful) in the amenities of Allah; so Allah made it taste the garment of hunger and fear for the things they were working out (i.e., doing)"
  16,113,"And indeed a Messenger from among them already came to them, then they cried him lies; so the torment took them (away) and they were unjust"
  16,114,"So eat of what Allah has provided you, lawfully good, and thank (Him) for the favor of Allah, in case it be Him only that you do worship"
  16,115,"Surely He has prohibited for you only carrion, (i.e., deal meat) and blood, and the flesh of swine, and what has been acclaimed to other than Allah. Yet whoever is constrained, without being inequitable or aggressive, then surely Allah is Ever-Forgiving, Ever-Merciful"
  16,116,"And do not say, as to what your tongues describe lying, (i.e., falsely, livingly) \"This is lawful and this is prohibited, \" so you may fabricate lies against Allah; surely the ones who fabricate lies against Allah will not prosper"
  16,117,A little enjoyment and they will have a painful torment
  16,118,"And for the ones who Judaized, (i.e., adopt Judaism) We have prohibited for them what we narrated to you earlier and in no way did We do them an injustice, but to themselves they were doing injustice"
  16,119,"Thereafter, surely your Lord ?? to the ones who do odious (deeds) in ignorance, thereafter repent ever after that and act righteously-surely your Lord after that is indeed Ever-Forgiving, Ever-Merciful"
  16,120,"Surely, Ibrahim (Abraham) was a nation, (i.e., a leader,Imam) devout to Allah, unswervingly upright, and he was not of the associators, (Those who associate others with Allah)"
  16,121,Thankful for His amenities. He selected him and He guided him to a straight Path
  16,122,"And We brought him in the present (life) (Literally: the lowly \"life\", i.e., the life of this world) a fair (reward), and surely in the Hereafter he will indeed be among the righteous"
  16,123,"Thereafter We revealed to you, (saying): \"Closely follow the creed of Ibrahim, (Abraham) unswervingly upright, and in no way was he one of the associators.\" (Those who associate others with Allah)"
  16,124,Surely the Sabbath was made only for the ones who differed about it; and surely your Lord will indeed judge between them on the Day of the Resurrection concerning (the things) about which they used to differ
  16,125,"Call (This is addressed to the Prophet) to the way of your Lord with wisdom and fair admonition, and dispute with them in the way (which is) fairest. Surely your Lord is The Best Knower of the ones who have erred away from His way, and He is The Best Knower of the right-guided"
  16,126,"And in case you (This is addressed to all believers) punish, then punish with the like of that wherewith you were punished; and indeed in case you endure patiently, indeed it is more charitable of the patient"
  16,127,"And (endure) patiently, and in no way is your patience with the help of anyone except with Allah. And do not grieve for them, nor be straitened for whatever they scheme"
  16,128,Surely Allah is with the ones who have been pious and the ones who are fair-doers